<div id="outline-container-sec-1-2" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-2">Cheating is not a new problem</h3>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-3" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-3">Why do students cheat?</h3>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-4" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-4">Brent/Atkisson (2011) study</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-4">
<p>
The authors site a classic study by Sykes and Matza (1957) that postulates five neutralization techniques. 
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-4-1" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-4-1">Five Neutralizations</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Denial of reponsibility
</li>
<li>Denial of injury
</li>
<li>Denial of the victim
</li>
<li>Condemnation of the condemners
</li>
<li>Appeal to higher authority
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-5" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-5">Technology is not a perfect solution, but ITS does offer several ways to help reduce the problem.</h3>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-6">Ways to prevent/reduce cheating</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-6">
</div><div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-1" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-1">Blackboard</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Set up a well-organized site that is easy for students to use
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Clear Course Objectives
</li>
<li>Clear Path to all discussions, assignments, and assessments
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Include useful documentation
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Syllabus: Clearly outline your expectations, and what to do if they have a problem
</li>
<li>Bb Testing Taking tips
</li>
<li>Links to the ITS Homepage, Java, etc.
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Group Assignments
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Break assignments down, and make each student accountable at every step
</li>
<li>Moderate/supervise projects at key mileposts
</li>
<li>Delegate authority
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-2" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-2">Blackboard Retention Center</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-2">
<p>
<i>Blackboard Retention Center is a new tool that replaces the Early Warning System. It helps instructors view student progress and target students who are falling behind. You can create custom rules, but the defaults are very powerful and allow you to use the feature out of the box.</i>
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-3" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-3">Wimba/Bb Collaborate</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-3">
<p>
Wimba and Bb Collaborate are both actively supported for SP2013 at UMKC, but Blackboard will no longer (get language from website)
We recommend that instructors begin transitioning to Bb Collaborate.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-4" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-4">Bb Collaborate</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-4">
<p>
Bb Collaborate allows instructors to interact with students in real-time.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Voice/Video chat
</li>
<li>Typed (IM) chat
</li>
<li>Simple polling options (e.g., raising hands, check marks, etc.)
</li>
<li>PowerPoint Presentations and whiteboard collaboration
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-5" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-5">Bb Collaborate</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-5">
<p>
Conduct your lessons completely online&#x2026;
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-6" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-6">Bb Collaborate</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-6">
<p>
Or hold Virtual Office Hours!
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-7" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-7">Blackboard Tests</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-7">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Create randomized questions/answers
</li>
<li>Assign different questions to each student
</li>
<li>Do not include anything that was not covered in class or the readings
</li>
<li>Encourage students to set up their computers correctly before the test 
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Use a 'practice test'
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Respondus LockDown Browser and Tegrity Proctoring are useful supplements to prevent cheating (They can be used together to remotely proctor student exams).
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-8" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-8">Respondus LockDown Browser</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-8">
<p>
Prevents students from accessing other websites or chat programs
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-9" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-9">Tegrity Proctoring</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-9">
<p>
Provides visual supervision of students as they take the test.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-10" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-10">Turnitin Assignments</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-10">
<p>
<a href="http://www.umkc.edu/ia/it/turnitin/">http://www.umkc.edu/ia/it/turnitin/</a>
Turnitin includes three integrated tools:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Orginality Review (plagarism detection tool)
</li>
<li>GradeMark (paperless grading system)
</li>
<li>PeerMark (peer evaluation review)
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-11" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-11">Creating a Turnitin Assignment in Blackboard</h4>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-12" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-12">Submitting a paper through the Turnitin website</h4>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-6-13" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1-6-13">I suspect my students of cheating? What next?</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-6-13">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>First, organize your thoughts. Make a note of all the details (e.g., the name of the assignment, the date range, why you suspect the student) 
</li>
<li>Contact our office with these details. We might need more information or authorization from a Department Chair or Dean.
</li>
<li>We'll do our best to find as much evidence as we can to help you make a determination.
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
